24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.109eb9f2-d94a-4083-94ab-52d8b24c0c94.prompt=Notification option\: 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.18f2c88b-1a71-43eb-93ec-b2770ba4d6ee.description=Iterates through a list of values. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.341aa634-d2d1-4302-9231-906c98fa2ec3.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.a3f31c5b-1827-429b-8b42-b74848e04e79.prompt=username 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.a622786b-4f80-4d9b-a669-5912e7671fe8.prompt=Threshold for maximum acceptable average latency 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.bdee0aef-f2d7-4fca-a601-41a9b0a7a12f.prompt=Notification method 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.c624bf5b-5c72-4950-a299-7a38e7aa7750.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifydata - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifyData to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processin tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requireing authentication. password - The password for username. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.c624bf5b-5c72-4950-a299-7a38e7aa7750.prompt=Here is your diagnostic for ${host} 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.d06858eb-7e9a-4efd-b37d-a5f7251784c8.prompt=Server Name - The name of the server to test the connection to. 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.d5c35cd0-5acb-4211-8dd2-6436d3e81950.prompt=Percentage of packet loss that is considered acceptable. 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.description=
Checks to see whether or not a connection exists, and if it exists checks to see if it is adequately reliable. Diagnoses what is wrong with the connection from multiple hosts..

Inputs\:
hosts - a comma separated list of the hosts to ping from.
target - the host to ping
delimiter - The delimiter for hosts.
lossThreshold - What percentage of packet loss you consider to be acceptable for this connection.
latencyThreshold - How long (in milliseconds) you consider to be an acceptable latency for this connection.
diagnostic so far - The result of previous diagnosis, used for chaining.
maxhops - How many hops traceroute diagnostic will descend.
notifyMethod - How to report the diagnostic.
username - username for hosts.
password - password for hosts.

Responses\:
success - no problems found.
diagnosed - problems found.
failure - something went wrong.

Recommended Thresholds\:

Connection Type		Loss Threshold (%)	Latency Threshold (ms)
DSL modem			2		200
Cable modem		2		200
dialup modem		2		500
ISDN Line			2		150
T1/T3/OCR			2		80
10 ethernet			2		10
Wireless			2		600
24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.e9281e11-c489-46f4-b4de-852212f0d97a.prompt=Threshold for maximum acceptable average latency 24b860ca-078e-4d4c-9d3d-08cb9b13c9d8.f0f8d3e7-615a-4e8b-b8d6-dc59e4f5f40f.prompt=Server Name - The name of the server to test the connection to.
